<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,337,868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,370,589,615]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Recognition:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[370,606,590,616]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lepidoziaceae" genus="Lepidozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="obtusiloba">
<emphasis box="[370,606,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Lepidozia obtusiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has leaf and underleaf margins crenulated due to bulging trigones between marginal cells, a region of enlarged cells at leaf base indistinct or absent, first two leaf lobes closely spaced, isodiametric terminal cells on underleaf lobes and leaf lobes, no accessory teeth on lobes or underleaves, and a more or less longitudinal-incubous leaf insertion line.
</paragraph>
